Nyandarua independent candidates have unanimously resolved to support President Uhuru Kenyatta and DP William Ruto&rsquo;s reelection.They also decided to fight to ensure the defeat of &ldquo;illegitimate JP candidates in the county since they are products of shambolic party primaries&rdquo;.They met yesterday at the Mood Hotel, Ol Kalou, where they also resolved to support independent governor candidate Moses Kiarie, alias, Badilisha.&ldquo;We have agreed that we shall campaign for Uhuru as we also seek our votes,&rdquo; Nyandarua Deputy Governor Waithaka Mwangi said. Mwangi lost in the JP primaries and is now Badilisha&rsquo;s running mate. There are 83 independent candidates in Nyandarua. Badilisha said this group should not be underrated since they wield unrivalled influence.